<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-08T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.51/1132: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-08T18:00:00+01:00">March 8, 1937—6
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>34. Your telegram No. 19, March 5. My telegram No. 33, March 7.<note n="22" xml:id="d412fn22">Not printed.</note> Informed at
                                Ministry of Foreign Affairs that in spite of British pressure
                                commitment will be lived up to. Coupons sterling issue due April 15
                                will be paid in full but as regards other coupons Polish proposal to
                                British [is] identic with proposal made American bondholders.
                                Confirmed this information Ministry of Finance.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>